 There is a second assumption in that there can be only one true interpretation to the written word, therefore can only convey one meaning. If that was true we would'nt have college courses dealing with various interpretations of Dante', Chaucer, Tolstoy, Melville and Tolkein to name a few. This does not necessarily mean that what you intended to mean was not true, just that it could have been left open to interpretation.<br>
 Last you seem to believe that since you are a writer you somehow have a better understanding on how to communicate at a personal level. Knowing personally several writers, Kathlene Sky, David Gerrold, The late Isaac Asimov means that I have had some insight with writers abilities to communicate, and with the exception of Mr Asimov the others although great writers had great difficulty expressing themselve personally through the writen medium. They were only a few but did have one thing you have not yet displayed and that is the realization of their deficits and so had to spend a heck of alot more time writing in those areas than in other areas.<br>
 Maybe you do spend time, yet I have seen them spend days composing simple replies to letters and you have made several posts in one day.<br>
 I and the others who have posted here are no better or worse than you but we do offer something to you and each other that perhaps you should consider a bit more that being an outside perspective. True subjective but this does not diminish its value.<br>
<br>
